\begin_layout Subsection*
2.1.1 Linear Algebra 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
1
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $l_{2}$
\end_inset

 be an Euclidean norm: 
\begin_inset Formula $\forall v\in\mathbb{R}^{d}:\,\left\Vert v\right\Vert _{2}=\sqrt{\sum v_{i}^{2}}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 be a corresponding matrix of 
\begin_inset Formula $T:V\rightarrow W$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is orthogonal, then:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\forall x\in V\,\,\left\Vert Ax\right\Vert _{2}^{2}=(Ax)^{T}(Ax)=x^{T}A^{T}Ax=
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\overbrace{=}^{A\,is\,orthogonal}x^{T}Ix=x^{T}x=\left\Vert x\right\Vert _{2}^{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since each norm holds: 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\Vert \cdot\right\Vert \geq0$
\end_inset

, we get:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\forall x\in V\,\,\left\Vert Ax\right\Vert _{2}^{2}=\left\Vert x\right\Vert _{2}^{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\iff
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\forall x\in V\,\,\left\Vert Ax\right\Vert _{2}=\left\Vert x\right\Vert _{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any two norms on a finite-dimensional vector space are equivalent, so:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\forall x\in V\,\,\left\Vert Ax\right\Vert =\left\Vert x\right\Vert \Rightarrow T\,\,is\,\,isometric\,\,tranformation
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
2
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Conversely, given the SVD of 
\begin_inset Formula $A=UÎ£V^{T}$
\end_inset

 we can recover the EVD of 
\begin_inset Formula $A^{T}A$
\end_inset

 or of 
\begin_inset Formula $AA^{T}$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
AA^{T}=\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 1 & 0\\
1 & -1 & 2
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 1\\
1 & -1\\
0 & 2
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{cc}
2 & 0\\
0 & 6
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It holds:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
AA^{T}=\left(U\Sigma V^{T}\right)\left(U\Sigma V^{T}\right)^{T}=U\Sigma V^{T}V\Sigma^{T}U^{T}=U\Sigma\Sigma^{T}U^{T}-EVD\,\,of\,\,AA^{T}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
A^{T}A=\left(U\Sigma V^{T}\right)^{T}\left(U\Sigma V^{T}\right)=V\Sigma^{T}U^{T}U\Sigma V^{T}=V\Sigma^{T}\Sigma V^{T}-EVD\,\,of\,\,A^{T}A
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\iff
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
AA^{T}=\left[\begin{array}{cc}
2 & 0\\
0 & 6
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 0\\
0 & 1
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{cc}
2 & 0\\
0 & 6
\end{array}\right]\left[\begin{array}{cc}
1 & 0\\
0 & 1
\end{array}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

